{
  "texts": [
    "Furthermore, we hold all DNNs in the DNN zoo in memory to avoid disk IO overhead.",
    "Placement of system components On a stand-alone, multi-GPU server, the dispatcher, scheduler, and each worker run in their own processes on the same machine.",
    "Therefore, the server should have sufficient download network bandwidth, enough CPU cores to run each process on dedicated cores, sufficient DRAM to hold the DNN zoo and store incoming requests (aggregate of all clients).",
    "On distributed servers, the dispatcher and scheduler processes run on a front-end machine, whereas workers run on separate machines where GPUs are installed.",
    "The front-end machine should be a powerful server to handle connections from multiple clients."
  ]
}